The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Tuesday, June 03, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Tuesday, June 3, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Chowringhee. Barricaded for flyover construction.				 																																	AJC Bose Road. A flyover is coming up.				 																Hard Talk				 																																	M.K. Singh, deputy commissioner (traffic), will meet readers of The Telegraph in his office at the Lalbazar police headquarters at 5 pm.				 																Drama fest				 																																	Sampreeti, an inter-club drama festival presented by Outram Club, at Gyan Manch. International Club will stage Smriti Sudha at 7 pm. Babuder Dalkukure by Dalhousie Institute at 8.15 pm.				 																Workshops				 																																	A workshop on Chhau dance of Saraikela, organised by Eastern Zonal Cultural Centre, at Aikatan, Salt Lake, 10 am to 5 pm.				 																																	A summer workshop for youngsters on modern dance, theatre, creative expression and folk dance at Padatik.				 																Photos				 																																	Landscapes, an exhibition of photographs by Soumitra Datta, at Academy of Fine Arts.				 																																	Bhavna, a display of photographs and paintings, at Academy of Fine Arts, North Gallery, 3 pm-8 pm.				 																Pottery				 																																	An exhibition of pottery at Central Cottage Industries Emporium from 10 am to 7 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	A retrospective of the works of Sunil Das at ITC Sonar Bangla Art Gallery, from 11 am to 7 pm.
